# Project Ecosystem

## DoneThat Projects
This repository (`donethat-electron`) is part of a larger ecosystem of DoneThat applications:

### Desktop Application (This Repository)
- Electron-based desktop application
- Handles local system integration
- Captures user activity (windows, keystrokes, audio, screenshots)
- Communicates with the backend service

### Web Application (Separate Repository)
- Web-based user interface
- Dashboard and analytics
- User settings and preferences
- Not included in this repository
- Repository: `donethat-web`

### Backend Service (Separate Repository)
- API server
- Data storage and processing
- Authentication and authorization
- Integration with third-party services
- Not included in this repository
- Repository: `donethat-backend`

## Integration Points
- Desktop app communicates with backend via REST API
- Web app shares authentication with desktop app
- Both apps use the same backend service
- Data synchronization between desktop and web interfaces

## Development Workflow
When working on features that span multiple projects:
1. Backend changes should be implemented first
2. Desktop app changes can be tested against staging backend
3. Web app changes can be tested against staging backend
4. All changes should be coordinated across repositories
